# Source vs Generated Reference (Human-Level)

Why this looks split:
1. Source templates are where humans should edit startup UI.
2. Generated files are auto-produced from source.
3. Runtime/build files are what launches and gets packaged.

Mental model:
- Source = recipe.
- Generated = prep output.
- Runtime/build = plated dish users see.

If you patch only generated/runtime files, regeneration can overwrite your work.
If you patch only source files, changes are durable but may not appear until regenerate/rebuild runs.

Primary source templates (edit first):
1. applications/browser/resources/preload.html
2. applications/electron/resources/preload.html
3. applications/electron-next/resources/preload.html

Common generated/runtime mirrors:
1. applications/browser/src-gen/frontend/index.html
2. applications/browser/lib/frontend/index.html
3. applications/electron/src-gen/frontend/index.html
4. applications/electron-next/src-gen/frontend/index.html
5. applications/electron-next/lib/frontend/index.html

Team workflow rule:
1. Edit source templates first.
2. Regenerate/rebuild target.
3. Validate running target.
4. Only hotfix generated/runtime when needed, then backport immediately to source.

